i7z crashes shortly after execution on HP ProBook 450 G1.  Using Fedora 23.  i7z ran without problems on same hardware when using F22.

Thanks for your report. I'm able to reproduce the crash.

There's an upstream issue indicating i7z_GUI is not developed further.
https://github.com/ajaiantilal/i7z/issues/1

I've found an entry in log about SELinux, maybe it's related. But I get that also with setenforce 0. Let's ask at SELinux maintainers, maybe they know something and can explain?
audit[6406]: ANOM_ABEND auid=1000 uid=0 gid=0 ses=1 subj=unconfined_u:unconfined_r:unconfined_t:s0-s0:c0.c1023 pid=6406 comm="i7z_GUI" exe="/home/builder/fedora-scm/i7z/i7z-5023138d7c35c4667c938b853e5ea89737334e92/GUI/i7z_GUI" sig=11

(In reply to Gordon Martin from comment #0)
…
> Truncated backtrace:
> Thread no. 1 (2 frames)
>  #0 Print_Information_Processor at ../helper_functions.c:486
>  #1 MyWidget::MyWidget at i7z_GUI.cpp:464

#0  Print_Information_Processor (nehalem=0x7fffa60c93c0, sandy_bridge=0x7fffa60c93c4, ivy_bridge=0x7fffa60c93c8, haswell=0xa60c93cc) at ../helper_functions.c:486
486	                *haswell = true;

No idea how this can cause the crash. So that does not make it less confusing.
Taking back. I can reproduce and have a fix.
